<p>The \(ATE\) here would be the mean of the last column, that is, of the treatment effect:</p>

<p>\(ATE=(-50 + 0 - 200 + 50)/4 = -50\)</p>

<p>The \(ATET\) here would be the mean of the last column when \(T=1\):</p>

<p>\(ATET=(- 200 + 50)/2 = -75\)</p>

<p>This is saying that, for the schools that were treated, the tablets reduced the academic performance of students, on average, by 75 points. Now, of course we can never know this. In reality, the table above would look like this:</p>

<p>\(ATE\) á»Ÿ Ä‘Ã¢y lÃ  trung bÃ¬nh cá»™ng cá»§a cá»™t cuá»‘i cÃ¹ng (tÃ¡c Ä‘á»™ng can thiá»‡p):</p>

<p>\(ATE=(-50 + 0 - 200 + 50)/4 = -50\)</p>

<p>\(ATET\) á»Ÿ Ä‘Ã¢y lÃ  trung bÃ¬nh cá»™ng cá»§a cá»™t cuá»‘i cÃ¹ng khi mÃ  \(T=1\):</p>

<p>\(ATET=(- 200 + 50)/2 = -75\)</p>

<p>Äiá»u nÃ y nghÄ©a lÃ  vá»›i cÃ¡c trÆ°á»ng nháº­n can thiá»‡p, tÃ­nh trung bÃ¬nh, mÃ¡y tÃ­nh báº£ng lÃ m giáº£m káº¿t quáº£ há»c táº­p cá»§a há»c sinh 75 Ä‘iá»ƒm. Táº¥t nhiÃªn chÃºng ta khÃ´ng bao giá» biáº¿t rÃµ nhÆ° tháº¿. Báº£ng sá»‘ liá»‡u trÃªn Ä‘Ã¢y thá»±c táº¿ trÃ´ng giá»‘ng tháº¿ nÃ y:</p>

